Package sprouts

Interface Vars<T extends @Nullable Object>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of the properties.
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<T>, Observable, Vals<T>
public interface Vars<T extends @Nullable Object> extends Vals<T>
A list of mutable properties that can be observed for changes by Subscriber types (see Observer and Action). Contrary to the supertype Vals, this interface provides methods for mutating the list. Use the Vals.onChange(Action) method to register change listeners to the list.
Use Observable.subscribe(Observer) if you want to be notified of changes to the list without any further information about the change.

Note that the name of this class is short for "variables". This name was deliberately chosen because it is short, concise and yet clearly conveys the same meaning as other names used to model this kind of pattern, like "properties", "observable objects", "observable values", "observable properties", etc.

Please take a look at the living sprouts documentation where you can browse a large collection of examples demonstrating how to use the API of this class.
